Cape Town - The body of a 68-year-old man was found at the scene of a house fire in Strand early on Tuesday. City Fire and Rescue Services spokesperson Jermaine Carelse said they were alerted to the fire at a house in Seventh Street at about 1.30am. “The caller stated the fire was spreading to adjacent houses and there were children trapped inside. Upon arrival at the scene, the fire crew immediately attended to the fire,” said Carelse. “Fire crews arrived quickly and managed to contain and extinguish the fire by 2am. “The crew found the body of a man who was unconscious and had been dragged to a nearby neighbour’s house. "Fire Service medics and metro ambulance staff tried to resuscitate him to no avail. The children were found safe and unharmed,” Carelse said. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said an inquest docket had been opened. Strand councillor Jongidumo Maxheke said he would be working with the Disaster and Risk management team to assist the bereaved family. Cape Argus Do you have something on your mind; or want to comment on the big stories of the day? We would love to hear from you. Please send your letters to arglet@inl.co.za. All letters to be considered for publication, must contain full names, addresses and contact details (not for publication). IOL is committed to freedom of speech as long as it is not derogatory or harmful to others.